  <brief_title>Obturator Nerve Block With Femoral and Sciatic Block</brief_title>
  <official_title>Is an Obturator Nerve Block Required for Every Patient Having Total Knee Arthroplasty With Femoral and Sciatic Nerve Block?</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Saint Francis Care</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Saint Francis Care</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate how many patients require the addition of the
      obturator nerve block in the recovery room after the total knee surgery. Also to study the
      efficacy of blocking the obturator nerve in controlling their knee pain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
